# Project Configuration

This file defines the Jira projects, statuses, and template references used across all skills and orchestrators. Update this file when your project context changes.

---

## Jira Projects

Projects that this BA Operating System manages:

| Project Key | Name / Description |
|-------------|-------------------|
| MYPROJECT   | Replace with your project name |

---

## Refinement Assessment Statuses

When running `/assess-refinement`, the system fetches all issues from these statuses:

| Status             | Purpose                                      |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Ready for Review   | Replace with your pre-refinement status      |
| In Refinement      | Replace with your refinement status          |

---

## Issue Template References

Read from local cache (`.cache/templates/`). Cache is populated on first use via MCP (read-through) or manually via `/refresh-templates`. Cache is gitignored — refresh when templates change upstream.

| Issue Type | Jira Key      | Cache file                         |
|------------|---------------|-----------------------------------|
| Story      | MYPROJECT-100 | `.cache/templates/story.md`        |
| Task       | MYPROJECT-101 | `.cache/templates/task.md`         |
| Bug        | MYPROJECT-102 | `.cache/templates/bug.md`          |

---

## Quality Reference

| Resource                    | Location         | Cache file                            |
|-----------------------------|------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Quality Management Playbook | Confluence page ID: 0000000000 | `.cache/templates/playbook.md` |
